Articles.Content:
About your patch 

    @PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleEngines]]:Final {	MODULE	{		name = tjs_EngineLight		lightPower = 1.0		lightRange = 40.0	}}@PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleEnginesFX]]:Final {	MODULE	{		name = tjs_EngineLightFX		lightPower = 1.0		lightRange = 40.0	}}

 Why can't you just have ? 

    @PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleEngines*]]:Final {	MODULE	{		name = tjs_EngineLightFX		lightPower = 1.0		lightRange = 40.0	}

I forked your Repo and played around with it. Some nice people on the #KSPMODDERS IRC helped out, and now you can haz custom colors. Pull request created.

Config file can now look like this:

    @PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleEngines]]:Final {	MODULE	{		name = tjs_EngineLight		lightPower = 1.0		lightRange = 40.0		lightRed = 1		lightGreen = 0.88f		lightBlue = 0.68f	}}@PART[*]:HAS[@MODULE[ModuleEnginesFX]]:Final {	MODULE	{		name = tjs_EngineLightFX		lightPower = 1.0		lightRange = 40.0		lightRed = 1		lightGreen = 0.88f		lightBlue = 0.68f	}}

